        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1 Podocinella misella(Berlese, 1913). Adult female. A – Antiaxial view of chelicera; B – Palpus; C – Epistome; D – Hypostome; E – Dorsal view of idiosoma; F – Detail of the lateral concavity. G – Ventral view of idiosoma; H – Tritosternum. Lyrifissures and pores enlarged for improved visibility. Based on specimens collected in Jaboticabal, Brazil." ;
